    "Name": "Hyperion",
    "Details": "The Hyperion was developed in response to the Omega's debut by the Word of Blake during the Jihad. Using Clan tech to make the structure and engine allowed for a massive 72.5 tons of available pod space for the Omnimech. Propelled by a 375 XL engine and built on an Endo-Steel framework the designers did have to cut some slight corners on the actual armor to allow for such extensive firepower, the mech is protected by 18.5 tons of ferro fibrous armor, which is one and a half tons below the maximum for the frame.  The C configuration mounts two gauss rifles and 4 LRM 20's boosted by Artemis IV.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
